            "id": "coma",
            "title": "Key Facts for Providers \u2013 How to Assess the NYI for Coma",
            "content": "The AVPU scale is used to assess a newborn/infant\u2019s level of consciousness.",
            "subsections": [
                {
                    "title": "AVPU Scale",
                    "items": [
                        "A \u2013 Alert",
                        "V \u2013 Responds to Voice",
                        "P \u2013 Responds to Pain (rub sternum)",
                        "U \u2013 Unresponsive to voice/shake and pain \u2192 Unconscious"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "assessment",
            "title": "How to Assess for Convulsions",
            "content": "Assessment is based on observation of the child and history from the parent. Seizures in neonates may be subtle (facial twitching, apnea, lip\u2011smacking, eye/hand/foot movements).",
            "subsections": [
                {
                    "title": "Common Causes in Neonates (percent prevalence)",
                    "table": [
                        {
                            "cause": "Hypoxic\u2011Ischaemic Encephalopathy (HIE)",
                            "prevalence": "38\u201148%"
                        },
                        {
                            "cause": "Hypoglycaemia",
                            "prevalence": "3\u20117.5%"
                        },
                        {
                            "cause": "Hypocalcaemia",
                            "prevalence": "2.3\u20119%"
                        },
                        {
                            "cause": "Central Nervous System infections",
                            "prevalence": "5.5\u201110.3%"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "compare",
            "title": "Comparing Tetanus and Convulsions",
            "content": "",
            "table": [
                {
                    "Tetanus": "Conscious",
                    "Convulsions": "Unconscious"
                },
                {
                    "Tetanus": "Increases with tactile stimulation, wind, light and noise",
                    "Convulsions": "Does not change in response to stimulation"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
